{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":6000,"text":"Well, first of all, let me thank Emeka -- as a matter of fact,"},{"time":11000,"text":"TED Global -- for putting this conference together."},{"time":16000,"text":"This conference is going to rank as the most important"},{"time":22000,"text":"in the beginning of the 21st century."},{"time":25000,"text":"Think African governments will put together a conference like this?"},{"time":28000,"text":"You think the A.U. will put together a conference like this?"},{"time":32000,"text":"Even before they do that they will ask for foreign aid."},{"time":36000,"text":"I would also like to pay homage and honor to the TED Fellows"},{"time":45000,"text":"June Arunga, James Shikwati, Andrew, and the other TED Fellows."},{"time":53000,"text":"I call them the Cheetah Generation."},{"time":57000,"text":"The Cheetah Generation is a new breed of Africans"},{"time":60000,"text":"who brook no nonsense about corruption."},{"time":63000,"text":"They understand what accountability and democracy is."},{"time":68000,"text":"They're not going to wait for government to do things for them."},{"time":72000,"text":"That's the Cheetah Generation,"},{"time":74000,"text":"and Africa's salvation rests on the backs of these Cheetahs."},{"time":79000,"text":"In contrast, of course, we have the Hippo Generation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":85000,"text":"The Hippo Generation are the ruling elites."},{"time":88000,"text":"They are stuck in their intellectual patch."},{"time":92000,"text":"Complaining about colonialism and imperialism,"},{"time":96000,"text":"they wouldn't move one foot."},{"time":98000,"text":"If you ask them to reform the economies,"},{"time":101000,"text":"they're not going to reform it"},{"time":103000,"text":"because they benefit from the rotten status quo."},{"time":106000,"text":"Now, there are a lot of Africans who are very angry,"},{"time":108000,"text":"angry at the condition of Africa."},{"time":113000,"text":"Now, we're talking about a continent that is not poor."},{"time":117000,"text":"It is rich in mineral resources, natural mineral resources."},{"time":122000,"text":"But the mineral wealth of Africa is not being utilized"},{"time":126000,"text":"to lift its people out of poverty."},{"time":129000,"text":"That's what makes a lot of Africans very angry."},{"time":133000,"text":"And in a way, Africa is more than a tragedy, in more ways than one."},{"time":139000,"text":"There's another enduring tragedy, and that tragedy is that"},{"time":143000,"text":"there are so many people, so many governments,"},{"time":146000,"text":"so many organizations who want to help the people in Africa."},{"time":150000,"text":"They don't understand."},{"time":154000,"text":"Now, we're not saying don't help Africa."},{"time":156000,"text":"Helping Africa is noble."},{"time":159000,"text":"But helping Africa has been turned into a theater of the absurd."},{"time":165000,"text":"It's like the blind leading the clueless."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":172000,"text":"There are certain things that we need to recognize."},{"time":176000,"text":"Africa's begging-bowl leaks."},{"time":180000,"text":"Did you know that 40 percent of the wealth created in Africa"},{"time":183000,"text":"is not invested here in Africa?"},{"time":185000,"text":"It's taken out of Africa."},{"time":187000,"text":"That's what the World Bank says."},{"time":191000,"text":"Look at Africa's begging-bowl."},{"time":194000,"text":"It leaks horribly."},{"time":197000,"text":"There are people who think that we should pour more money,"},{"time":200000,"text":"more aid into this bowl which leaks."},{"time":205000,"text":"What are the leakages?"},{"time":208000,"text":"Corruption alone costs Africa 148 billion dollars a year."},{"time":215000,"text":"Yes, put that aside."},{"time":218000,"text":"Capital flight out of Africa, 80 billion a year."},{"time":223000,"text":"Put that aside."},{"time":226000,"text":"Let's take food imports."},{"time":228000,"text":"Every year Africa spends 20 billion dollars to import food."},{"time":235000,"text":"Just add that up, all these leakages."},{"time":238000,"text":"That's far more than the 50 billion Tony Blair wants to raise for Africa."},{"time":243000,"text":"Now, back in the 1960s Africa not only fed itself,"},{"time":246000,"text":"it also exported food."},{"time":248000,"text":"Not anymore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251000,"text":"We know that something has gone fundamentally wrong."},{"time":255000,"text":"You know it, I know it, but let's not waste our time"},{"time":258000,"text":"talking about these mistakes because we'll spend all day here."},{"time":263000,"text":"Let's move on, and flip over to the next chapter,"},{"time":269000,"text":"and that's what this conference is all about -- the next chapter."},{"time":273000,"text":"The next chapter begins with first of all, asking ourselves"},{"time":278000,"text":"this fundamental question,"},{"time":280000,"text":"\"Whom do we want to help in Africa?\""},{"time":285000,"text":"There is the people, and then there is the government or leaders."},{"time":291000,"text":"Now, the previous speaker before me,"},{"time":298000,"text":"Idris Mohammed, indicated that"},{"time":303000,"text":"we've had abysmal leadership in Africa."},{"time":308000,"text":"That characterization, in my view, is even more charitable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":317000,"text":"I belong to an Internet discussion forum,"},{"time":320000,"text":"an African Internet discussion forum,"},{"time":324000,"text":"and I asked them, I said, \"Since 1960, we've had exactly"},{"time":330000,"text":"204 African heads of state, since 1960.\""},{"time":334000,"text":"And I asked them to name me just 20 good leaders,"},{"time":338000,"text":"just 20 good leaders --"},{"time":341000,"text":"you may want to take this leadership challenge yourself."},{"time":346000,"text":"I asked them to name me just 20."},{"time":349000,"text":"Everybody mentioned Nelson Mandela, of course."},{"time":352000,"text":"Kwame Nkrumah, Nyerere, Kenyatta -- somebody mentioned Idi Amin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":362000,"text":"I let that pass."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":367000,"text":"My point is, they couldn't go beyond 15."},{"time":373000,"text":"Even if they had been able to name me 20,"},{"time":376000,"text":"what does that tell you?"},{"time":378000,"text":"20 out of 204 means that the vast majority"},{"time":385000,"text":"of the African leaders failed their people."},{"time":390000,"text":"And if you look at them, the slate of the post-colonial leaders --"},{"time":396000,"text":"an assortment of military fufu heads,"},{"time":400000,"text":"Swiss-bank socialists, crocodile liberators, vampire elites,"},{"time":405000,"text":"quack revolutionaries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"Now, this leadership is a far cry from the traditional leaders"},{"time":414000,"text":"that Africans have known for centuries."},{"time":417000,"text":"The second false premise that we make"},{"time":420000,"text":"when we're trying to help Africa"},{"time":421000,"text":"is that sometimes we think that there is something called"},{"time":427000,"text":"a government in Africa that cares about its people,"},{"time":433000,"text":"serves the interests of the people, and represents the people."},{"time":439000,"text":"There is one particular quote -- a Lesotho chief once said"},{"time":444000,"text":"that \"Here in Lesotho, we've got two problems:"},{"time":446000,"text":"rats and the government.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":449000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":453000,"text":"What you and I understand as a government"},{"time":456000,"text":"doesn't exist in many African countries."},{"time":459000,"text":"In fact, what we call our governments are vampire states."},{"time":464000,"text":"Vampires because they suck"},{"time":467000,"text":"the economic vitality out of their people."},{"time":470000,"text":"Government is the problem in Africa."},{"time":474000,"text":"A vampire state is the government --"},{"time":477000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":478000,"text":"-- which has been hijacked by a phalanx of bandits and crooks"},{"time":482000,"text":"who use the instruments of state power to enrich themselves,"},{"time":485000,"text":"their cronies, and tribesmen and exclude everybody else."},{"time":490000,"text":"The richest people in Africa are heads-of-state and ministers,"},{"time":494000,"text":"and quite often the chief bandit is the head-of-state himself."},{"time":500000,"text":"Where do they get their money?"},{"time":502000,"text":"By creating wealth?"},{"time":504000,"text":"No."},{"time":505000,"text":"By raking it off the backs of their suffering people."},{"time":509000,"text":"That's not wealth creation. It's wealth redistribution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515000,"text":"The third fundamental issue that we have to recognize"},{"time":520000,"text":"is that if we want to help the African people,"},{"time":525000,"text":"we must know where the African people are."},{"time":528000,"text":"Take any African economy."},{"time":531000,"text":"An African economy can be broken up into three sectors."},{"time":534000,"text":"There is the modern sector, there is the informal sector"},{"time":540000,"text":"and the traditional sector."},{"time":544000,"text":"The modern sector is the abode of the elites."},{"time":547000,"text":"It's the seat of government."},{"time":550000,"text":"In many African countries the modern sector is lost."},{"time":554000,"text":"It's dysfunctional."},{"time":556000,"text":"It is a meretricious fandango of imported systems,"},{"time":560000,"text":"which the elites themselves don't understand."},{"time":564000,"text":"That is the source of many of Africa's problems"},{"time":568000,"text":"where the struggles for political power emanate"},{"time":572000,"text":"and then spill over onto the informal and the traditional sector,"},{"time":577000,"text":"claiming innocent lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581000,"text":"Now the modern sector, of course,"},{"time":583000,"text":"is where a lot of the development aid and resources went into."},{"time":589000,"text":"More than 80 percent of Ivory Coast's development"},{"time":592000,"text":"went into the modern sector."},{"time":594000,"text":"The other sectors, the informal and the traditional sectors,"},{"time":600000,"text":"are where you find the majority of the African people,"},{"time":604000,"text":"the real people in Africa. That's where you find them."},{"time":607000,"text":"Now, obviously it makes common sense"},{"time":609000,"text":"that if you want to help the people, you go where the people are."},{"time":612000,"text":"But that's not what we did."},{"time":614000,"text":"As a matter of fact,"},{"time":616000,"text":"we neglected the informal and the traditional sectors."},{"time":623000,"text":"Now, traditional sector is where Africa produces its agriculture,"},{"time":627000,"text":"which is one of the reasons why Africa can't feed itself,"},{"time":630000,"text":"and that's why it must import food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634000,"text":"All right, you cannot develop Africa by ignoring"},{"time":638000,"text":"the informal and the traditional sectors."},{"time":642000,"text":"And you can't develop the informal and the traditional sectors"},{"time":648000,"text":"without an operational understanding of how these two sectors work."},{"time":654000,"text":"These two sectors, let me describe to you,"},{"time":656000,"text":"have their own indigenous institutions."},{"time":659000,"text":"First one is the political system."},{"time":663000,"text":"Traditionally, Africans hate governments. They hate tyranny."},{"time":667000,"text":"If you look into their traditional systems,"},{"time":670000,"text":"Africans organize their states in two types."},{"time":674000,"text":"The first one belongs to those ethnic societies"},{"time":679000,"text":"who believe that the state was necessarily tyrannous,"},{"time":683000,"text":"so they didn't want to have anything to do"},{"time":686000,"text":"with any centralized authority."},{"time":691000,"text":"These societies are the Ibo, the Somali, the Kikuyus,"},{"time":694000,"text":"for example. They have no chiefs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697000,"text":"The other ethnic groups, which did have chiefs,"},{"time":701000,"text":"made sure that they surrounded the chiefs"},{"time":705000,"text":"with councils upon councils upon councils"},{"time":708000,"text":"to prevent them from abusing their power."},{"time":713000,"text":"In Ashanti tradition, for example,"},{"time":716000,"text":"the chief cannot make any decision"},{"time":718000,"text":"without the concurrence of the council of elders."},{"time":721000,"text":"Without the council the chief can't pass any law,"},{"time":724000,"text":"and if the chief doesn't govern according to the will of the people"},{"time":727000,"text":"he will be removed."},{"time":729000,"text":"If not, the people will abandon the chief,"},{"time":733000,"text":"go somewhere else and set up a new settlement."},{"time":735000,"text":"And even if you look in ancient African empires,"},{"time":739000,"text":"they were all organized around one particular principle --"},{"time":744000,"text":"the confederacy principle,"},{"time":746000,"text":"which is characterized by a great deal of devolution of authority,"},{"time":750000,"text":"decentralization of power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":753000,"text":"Now, this is what I have described to you."},{"time":755000,"text":"This is part of Africa's indigenous political heritage."},{"time":759000,"text":"Now, compare that to the modern systems"},{"time":761000,"text":"the ruling elites established on Africa."},{"time":765000,"text":"It is a total far cry."},{"time":768000,"text":"In the economic system in traditional Africa,"},{"time":773000,"text":"the means of production is privately owned."},{"time":776000,"text":"It's owned by extended families."},{"time":779000,"text":"You see, in the West, the basic economic and social unit"},{"time":782000,"text":"is the individual."},{"time":784000,"text":"The American will say, \"I am because I am,"},{"time":787000,"text":"and I can damn well do anything I want, anytime.\""},{"time":789000,"text":"The accent is on the \"I.\""},{"time":792000,"text":"In Africa, the Africans say, \"I am, because we are.\""},{"time":796000,"text":"The \"we\" connotes community -- the extended family system."},{"time":800000,"text":"The extended family system pools its resources together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803000,"text":"They own farms. They decide what to do, what to produce."},{"time":807000,"text":"They don't take any orders from their chiefs."},{"time":810000,"text":"They decide what to do."},{"time":812000,"text":"And when they produce their crops, they sell the surplus"},{"time":816000,"text":"on marketplaces."},{"time":818000,"text":"When they make a profit it is theirs to keep,"},{"time":820000,"text":"not for the chief to sequester it from them."},{"time":823000,"text":"So, in a nutshell, what we had in traditional Africa"},{"time":827000,"text":"was a free-market system."},{"time":829000,"text":"There were markets in Africa"},{"time":831000,"text":"before the colonialists stepped foot on the continent."},{"time":833000,"text":"Timbuktu was one great big market town."},{"time":835000,"text":"Kano, Salaga -- they were all there."},{"time":837000,"text":"Even if you go to West Africa, you notice that market activity"},{"time":841000,"text":"in West Africa has always been dominated by women."},{"time":844000,"text":"So, it's quite appropriate that this section is called"},{"time":847000,"text":"a marketplace."},{"time":848000,"text":"The market is not alien to Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":851000,"text":"What Africans practiced was a different form of capitalism,"},{"time":855000,"text":"but then after independence, all of a sudden,"},{"time":858000,"text":"markets, capitalism became a western institution,"},{"time":862000,"text":"and the leaders said Africans were ready for socialism."},{"time":867000,"text":"Nonsense."},{"time":869000,"text":"And even then, what kind of socialism did they practice?"},{"time":872000,"text":"The socialism that they practiced was a peculiar form of"},{"time":875000,"text":"Swiss-bank socialism,"},{"time":877000,"text":"which allowed the heads of states and the ministers"},{"time":880000,"text":"to rape and plunder Africa's"},{"time":883000,"text":"treasuries for deposit in Switzerland."},{"time":885000,"text":"That is not the kind of system Africans had known for centuries."},{"time":889000,"text":"What do we do now?"},{"time":890000,"text":"Go back to Africa's indigenous institutions,"},{"time":893000,"text":"and this is where we charge the Cheetahs to go into the informal sectors,"},{"time":898000,"text":"the traditional sectors."},{"time":899000,"text":"That's where you find the African people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901000,"text":"And I'd like to show you a quick little video"},{"time":904000,"text":"about the informal sector, about the boat-building"},{"time":907000,"text":"that I, myself, tried to mobilize Africans in the Diaspora"},{"time":912000,"text":"to invest in."},{"time":913000,"text":"Could you please show that?"},{"time":943000,"text":"The men are going fishing in these small boats."},{"time":946000,"text":"Yes, it's an enterprise."},{"time":948000,"text":"This is by a local Ghanaian entrepreneur, using his own capital."},{"time":953000,"text":"He's getting no assistance from the government,"},{"time":955000,"text":"and he's building a second, bigger boat."},{"time":958000,"text":"A bigger boat will mean more fish will be caught and landed."},{"time":963000,"text":"It means that he will be able to employ more Ghanaians."},{"time":966000,"text":"It also means that he will be able to generate wealth."},{"time":970000,"text":"And then it will have what economists call"},{"time":974000,"text":"external effects on a local economy."},{"time":977000,"text":"All that you need to do, all that the elites need to do,"},{"time":980000,"text":"is to move this operation into something that is enclosed"},{"time":983000,"text":"so that the operation can be made more efficient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":986000,"text":"Now, it is not just this informal sector."},{"time":989000,"text":"There is also traditional medicine."},{"time":993000,"text":"80 percent of Africans still rely on traditional medicine."},{"time":996000,"text":"The modern healthcare sector has totally collapsed."},{"time":1000000,"text":"Now, this is an area -- I mean, there is a treasure trove of wealth"},{"time":1007000,"text":"in the traditional medicine area."},{"time":1009000,"text":"This is where we need to mobilize Africans,"},{"time":1012000,"text":"in the Diaspora especially, to invest in this."},{"time":1015000,"text":"We also need to mobilize Africans in the Diaspora,"},{"time":1018000,"text":"not only to go into the traditional sectors,"},{"time":1021000,"text":"but to go into agriculture and also to instigate change from within."},{"time":1027000,"text":"We were able to mobilize Ghanaians in the Diaspora"},{"time":1031000,"text":"to instigate change in Ghana and bring about democracy in Ghana."},{"time":1036000,"text":"And I know that with the Cheetahs, we can take Africa back"},{"time":1041000,"text":"one village at a time."},{"time":1043000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1044000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}